    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-02T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-02T21:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/781: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-02T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 2, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. We have read your telegram No. 1781 of December 26, 8 p.m. with interest and
                    fully approve the attitude taken by you during the conversation. The matter of
                    the Baltic gold, ships, Legations and so forth will be made the subject of a
                    subsequent telegram to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
